column1: #Text=at the end of last year , Wikinews interviewed several companies and groups about the feature .
#Text=DuckDuckGo
#Text=DuckDuckGo founder Gabriel Weinberg
#Text=Image : Gabriel Weinberg .
#Text=DuckDuckGo logo Image : Gabriel Weinberg .
#Text=DuckDuckGo office
#Text=Image : Gabriel Weinberg .
#Text=A crowdsourced search engine DuckDuckGo reviewed the feature and launched a whatisDNT microsite in December .
#Text=The review involved checking answers to basic questions such as whether websites stop shaping a user profile based on users ' online actvitity or stop displaying targeted advertising .
#Text=Wikinews interviewed DuckDuckGo founder Gabriel Weinberg about the microsite launch and the DuckDuckGo opinion on the feature .
#Text=What prompted the launch of DuckDuckGo ( I think it was around 2006 ? ) ?
#Text=We launched on Sep 25 , 2008 , though I had been working on it for about a year prior .
#Text=The initial motivation was to try a search engine with a different UI that did a better job of using more structured content ( like from Wikipedia ) and also more aggressively removed spam .
#Text=What does the DuckDuckGo Team use instead of Gmail ?
#Text=We do not have company mail accounts ( beyond forwarding ones ) , so everyone uses what they want .
#Text=I personally use outlook.com right now .
#Text=When and how did DuckDuckGo start using Perl ?
#Text=What influenced this decision and language choice ?
#Text=We started out in Perl .
#Text=I picked it up at MIT where it was prevalent in the late 90s , and pretty much never looked back .
#Text=It worked really well for a project like this that is text heavy and can use a lot of existing helper ( CPAN ) libraries .
#Text=How did you first hear about " DoNotTrack " feature ?

column1: #Text=I do not remember , but it was a long time ago : ) .
#Text=The Do Not Track concept was proposed many years ago .
#Text=When did you launch http://whatisDNT.com/ ?
#Text=Who worked on it ?
#Text=What researches , tests and studies did it involve ?
#Text=We launched the What Is Do Not Track micro-site on Dec 19 , 2012 , and various members of the DuckDuckGo Team worked on it ( including myself ) .
#Text=We had been following it closely for a while , and so have been up to date on everything that is going on with it .
#Text=It honestly does n't take any tests to prove its ineffectiveness since companies like Google tell you straight up they do n't honor it .
#Text=A search engine that does not track users sounds good .
#Text=What do you recommend users to do to not be tracked by *other* websites , such as blogs with targeted ads in sidebar ?
